    <mads:note type="history">AP 6.152</mads:note>
    <mads:note type="source">"Agis, a Greek poet, a native of Argos, and a contemporary of Alexander
      the Great, whom he accompanied on his Asiatic expedition.....The Greek Anthology (vi. 152)
      contains an epigram , which is probably the work of this flatterer...." from Smith's
      Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 1, 1867, p. 73.</mads:note>
    <mads:note type="source">"Agis, 5, epigrammatic poet, author of an epigram stemming from the
      ‘Garland’ of Meleager in which a hunter dedicates to Apollo a few modest tools with the
      promise of richer gifts, if only the god will provide him with a goodly bounty......." from
      Degani, Enzo (Bologna). "Agis." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik
      and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2007. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 18 July 2007</mads:note>
